\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line Although the evaluator indicated that Criteria 1\'2C 2 5\'2C 7 and 8 meet minimum standards\'2C concerns are expressed in terms of the distance education mode of delivery and the staff available at some of the campuses to teach on the programme. As with other programmes considered for this institution in recent times\'2C the programme will not be accredited for distance education. The teaching and learning strategy and methods appear to be appropriate to a contact mode of delivery and it is not clear how distance students will be supported and have access to library resources\'2C etc.\line \line The Diploma in Business Administration was submitted for accreditation as an HEQF-realigned version of an existing one which is not so aligned. As a result\'2C the realigned programme was approved by the institution\'E2\'80\'99s academic governance structures and Board of Directors on 25th March 2011. The programme is consonant with the institution\'E2\'80\'99s mission\'2C and goals. There are policies in place to govern the development of programmes and the allocation of necessary resources.  The programme application indicates the programme as having 370 Credit Points while the SAQA submission indicates 360. The institution needs to be consistent as a 10 credit point difference has implications for the notional hours calculated.\line \line The evaluator noted that the academic staff at the following sites do not comply with the minimum requirements to teach on the programme\'3A Vereeniging\'2C Bloemfontein \'28Maitland\'29 and Pietermaritzburg.  At the following sites academic staff are not fully compliant with the minimum requirements\'3A 1.Cape Town Campus\'2C 2.Main  Street - Johannesburg\'2C 3. Bloemfontein City Campus\'2C 4. Pietermaritzburg \'28Long Market\'29\'2C 5. Randburg\'2C 6. De Korte Street- Braamfontein\'2C  7. Jorrison street- Braamfontein\'2C 8. Krugersdorp and 9. Polokwane . The programme should therefore not be accredited for these sites. \line \line The Directorate recommends that the programme be accredited to be offered as a contact programme only at the following sites\'3A \'281\'29 Joe Slovo\'2C Durban\'2C \'282\'29 Church St.\'2C Pretoria\'3B \'283\'29 Struben St.\'2C Pretoria\'3B \'284\'29 Edenvale Campus\'2C Johannesburg\'3B \'285\'29  7 Wolf Street\'2C Kempton Park \'286\'29 Kempton Park Campus. The programme is not recommended for accreditation for the distance education mode and is not accredited to be offered at the sites that do not meet the required levels of academic staffing. \line \cell \pard 

